==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Parasphenoid
<hw>Par`a*sphe"noid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>para-</ets> + <ets>sphenoid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Near the sphenoid bone; -- applied especially to a bone situated
immediately beneath the sphenoid in the base of the skull in many
animals.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>The parasphenoid
bone.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

